results.question: How many singers do we have?
results.gold_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM singer
results.generated_sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT s.Singer_ID) AS num_singers
FROM singer s

results.question: What is the total number of singers?
results.gold_sql: SELECT count(*) FROM singer
results.generated_sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT s.Singer_ID) AS Total_Singers
FROM singer s

results.question: Show name, country, age for all singers ordered by age from the oldest to the youngest.
results.gold_sql: SELECT name ,  country ,  age FROM singer ORDER BY age DESC
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name, s.Country, s.Age
FROM singer AS s
JOIN singer_in_concert AS sic ON s.Singer_ID = sic.Singer_ID
JOIN concert AS c ON sic.concert_ID = c.concert_ID
ORDER BY s.Age DESC

results.question: What are the names, countries, and ages for every singer in descending order of age?
results.gold_sql: SELECT name ,  country ,  age FROM singer ORDER BY age DESC
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name, s.Country, s.Age
FROM singer AS s
JOIN concert_in_singer ON s.Singer_ID = concert_in_singer.Singer_ID
WHERE s.Is_male = 0
ORDER BY s.Age DESC

results.question: What is the average, minimum, and maximum age of all singers from France?
results.gold_sql: SELECT avg(age) ,  min(age) ,  max(age) FROM singer WHERE country  =  'France'
results.generated_sql:
SELECT AVG(age), MIN(age), MAX(age)
FROM singer
WHERE Country = 'France'

results.question: What is the average, minimum, and maximum age for all French singers?
results.gold_sql: SELECT avg(age) ,  min(age) ,  max(age) FROM singer WHERE country  =  'France'
results.generated_sql:
SELECT AVG(age), MIN(age), MAX(age)
FROM singer
WHERE country = 'France'

results.question: Show the name and the release year of the song by the youngest singer.
results.gold_sql: SELECT song_name ,  song_release_year FROM singer ORDER BY age LIMIT 1
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name AS "Singer Name", sr.Year AS "Release Year"
FROM singer s
JOIN singer_in_concert sic ON s.Singer_ID = sic.Singer_ID
JOIN concert c ON sic.concert_ID = c.concert_ID
JOIN song_release sr ON s.Song_Name = sr.Song_Name AND s.Song_release_year = sr.Year
WHERE s.Age = (SELECT MIN(Age) FROM singer)
ORDER BY 1, 2

results.question: What are the names and release years for all the songs of the youngest singer?
results.gold_sql: SELECT song_name ,  song_release_year FROM singer ORDER BY age LIMIT 1
results.generated_sql:
SELECT singer.Name AS Singer_Name, song.Song_release_year AS Song_Release_Year
FROM singer
JOIN concert ON singer.Singer_ID = concert.Singer_ID
JOIN singer_in_concert ON concert.concert_ID = singer_in_concert.concert_ID
JOIN song ON singer.Singer_ID = song.Singer_ID
WHERE singer.Age = (SELECT MIN(Age) FROM singer)

results.question: What are  the different countries with singers above age 20?

results.question: Show all countries and the number of singers in each country.

results.question: How many singers are from each country?

results.question: List all song names by singers above the average age.
results.gold_sql: SELECT song_name FROM singer WHERE age  >  (SELECT avg(age) FROM singer)
results.generated_sql:

FROM singer s
JOIN concert c ON s.Singer_ID = c.Singer_ID

ORDER BY s.Name

results.question: What are all the song names by singers who are older than average?

results.question: What is the name and capacity for the stadium with highest average attendance?

results.question: What is the name and capacity for the stadium with the highest average attendance?

results.question: Show the stadium name and capacity with most number of concerts in year 2014 or after.
results.gold_sql: SELECT T2.name ,  T2.capacity FROM concert AS T1 JOIN stadium AS T2 ON T1.stadium_id  =  T2.stadium_id WHERE T1.year  >=  2014 GROUP BY T2.stadium_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

results.question: What is the name and capacity of the stadium with the most concerts after 2013 ?

results.question: Find the name and location of the stadiums which some concerts happened in the years of both 2014 and 2015.

results.question: What are the names and locations of the stadiums that had concerts that occurred in both 2014 and 2015?

SELECT citizen.Citizenship AS country, COUNT(*) as number_of_singers
FROM singer
JOIN country on country.citizenship = singer.citizenship
GROUP BY citizenship

results.question: Please show the most common citizenship of singers.
results.gold_sql: SELECT Citizenship FROM singer GROUP BY Citizenship ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1
results.generated_sql:
SELECT citizenship, COUNT(*) as count
FROM singer
GROUP BY citizenship
ORDER BY count DESC
LIMIT 1

results.question: What is the most common singer citizenship ?
results.gold_sql: select citizenship from singer group by citizenship order by count(*) desc limit 1
results.generated_sql:
SELECT citizenship, COUNT(*) AS count
FROM singer
GROUP BY citizenship
ORDER BY count DESC
LIMIT 1

results.question: Show different citizenships and the maximum net worth of singers of each citizenship.
results.gold_sql: SELECT Citizenship ,  max(Net_Worth_Millions) FROM singer GROUP BY Citizenship
results.generated_sql:
SELECT DISTINCT s.Citizenship AS Citizenship, MAX(s.Net_Worth_Millions) AS Maximum_Net_Worth
FROM singer s
JOIN song so ON s.Singer_ID = so.Singer_ID
GROUP BY s.Citizenship
ORDER BY Maximum_Net_Worth DESC

results.question: For each citizenship, what is the maximum net worth?
results.gold_sql: SELECT Citizenship ,  max(Net_Worth_Millions) FROM singer GROUP BY Citizenship
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Citizenship AS Citizenship, MAX(s.Net_Worth_Millions) AS Maximum_Net_Worth
FROM singer AS s
GROUP BY s.Citizenship
ORDER BY Maximum_Net_Worth DESC

results.question: Show titles of songs and names of singers.
results.gold_sql: SELECT T2.Title ,  T1.Name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Title, s.Name
FROM singer AS s
INNER JOIN song AS so ON s.Singer_ID = so.Singer_ID

results.question: What are the song titles and singer names?
results.gold_sql: SELECT T2.Title ,  T1.Name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name AS Singer_Name, t.Title AS Song_Title
FROM singer s
JOIN song t ON t.Singer_ID = s.Singer_ID
ORDER BY t.Highest_Position

results.question: Show distinct names of singers that have songs with sales more than 300000.
results.gold_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID WHERE T2.Sales  >  300000
results.generated_sql:
SELECT DISTINCT s.Name
FROM singer s
JOIN song so ON s.Singer_ID = so.Singer_ID
WHERE so.Sales > 300000

results.question: what are the different names of the singers that have sales more than 300000?
results.gold_sql: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID WHERE T2.Sales  >  300000
results.generated_sql:
SELECT DISTINCT s.Name
FROM singer AS s
JOIN song AS so ON s.Singer_ID = so.Singer_ID
WHERE so.Sales > 300000

results.question: Show the names of singers that have more than one song.
results.gold_sql: SELECT T1.Name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID GROUP BY T1.Name HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name
FROM singer s
JOIN song so ON s.Singer_ID = so.Singer_ID
GROUP BY s.Name
HAVING COUNT(so.Song_ID) > 1

results.question: What are the names of the singers that have more than one songs?
results.gold_sql: SELECT T1.Name FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID GROUP BY T1.Name HAVING COUNT(*)  >  1
results.generated_sql:
SELECT singer.Name
FROM singer
JOIN song
ON singer.Singer_ID = song.Singer_ID
GROUP BY singer.Name
HAVING COUNT(song.Song_ID) > 1

results.question: Show the names of singers and the total sales of their songs.
results.gold_sql: SELECT T1.Name ,  sum(T2.Sales) FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID GROUP BY T1.Name
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name AS Singer_Name, SUM(song.Sales) AS Total_Sales
FROM singer s JOIN song ON s.Singer_ID = song.Singer_ID
GROUP BY s.Name
ORDER BY SUM(song.Sales) DESC

results.question: For each singer name, what is the total sales for their songs?
results.gold_sql: SELECT T1.Name ,  sum(T2.Sales) FROM singer AS T1 JOIN song AS T2 ON T1.Singer_ID  =  T2.Singer_ID GROUP BY T1.Name
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name AS Singer_Name, SUM(s.Sales) AS Total_Sales
FROM singer AS s
JOIN song AS t ON s.Singer_ID = t.Singer_ID
GROUP BY s.Name

results.question: List the name of singers that do not have any song.
results.gold_sql: SELECT Name FROM singer WHERE Singer_ID NOT IN (SELECT Singer_ID FROM song)
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name AS Singer_Name
FROM singer s
LEFT JOIN song so ON s.Singer_ID = so.Singer_ID
WHERE so.Song_ID IS NULL

results.question: What is the sname of every sing that does not have any song?
results.gold_sql: SELECT Name FROM singer WHERE Singer_ID NOT IN (SELECT Singer_ID FROM song)
results.generated_sql:
SELECT s.Name AS sname
FROM singer s
LEFT JOIN song so ON so.Singer_ID = s.Singer_ID
WHERE so.Song_ID IS NULL

results.question: Show the citizenship shared by singers with birth year before 1945 and after 1955.
results.gold_sql: SELECT Citizenship FROM singer WHERE Birth_Year  <  1945 INTERSECT SELECT Citizenship FROM singer WHERE Birth_Year  >  1955
results.generated_sql:
SELECT DISTINCT s.Citizenship
FROM singer AS s
JOIN song AS g ON s.Singer_ID = g.Singer_ID
WHERE s.Birth_Year < 1945 AND s.Birth_Year > 1955

results.question: What are the citizenships that are shared by singers with a birth year before 1945 and after 1955?
results.gold_sql: SELECT Citizenship FROM singer WHERE Birth_Year  <  1945 INTERSECT SELECT Citizenship FROM singer WHERE Birth_Year  >  1955
results.generated_sql:
SELECT DISTINCT citizenship
FROM singer
WHERE birth_year < 1945 AND birth_year > 1955

results.question: What is the feature type name of feature AirCon?
results.gold_sql: SELECT T2.feature_type_name FROM Other_Available_Features AS T1 JOIN Ref_Feature_Types AS T2 ON T1.feature_type_code  =  T2.feature_type_code WHERE T1.feature_name  =  "AirCon"

FROM Ref_Feature_Types

results.question: Show the property type descriptions of properties belonging to that code.
results.gold_sql: SELECT T2.property_type_description FROM Properties AS T1 JOIN Ref_Property_Types AS T2 ON T1.property_type_code  =  T2.property_type_code GROUP BY T1.property_type_code
results.generated_sql:
SELECT rpt.property_type_description
FROM Ref_Property_Types rpt
JOIN Properties p ON p.property_type_code = rpt.property_type_code

results.question: What are the names of properties that are either houses or apartments with more than 1 room?
results.gold_sql: SELECT property_name FROM Properties WHERE property_type_code  =  "House" UNION SELECT property_name FROM Properties WHERE property_type_code  =  "Apartment" AND room_count  >  1
results.generated_sql:
SELECT DISTINCT p.property_name
FROM Properties p
JOIN Ref_Property_Types pt ON p.property_type_code = pt.property_type_code
WHERE pt.property_type_description IN ('House', 'Apartment') AND room_count > 1
